{
  "doc_id": "46398",
  "text": "Plasma volume expansion of 5% albumin as a fraction of infused volume is shown to be in the range of 50-110% immediately after infusion in previous studies using a similar methodology in postoperative or in septic patients [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Our results extend these previous findings and show that the volume-expanding effect persists for at least 2.5 h after termination of the infusion.",
